Title:
Cobalt Strike CheatSheet

Type:
Documentation

Short Summary (4–8 sentences max):
- A curated cheat sheet of operational notes and command references for the Cobalt Strike C2 framework (Beacon).  
- It helps operators quickly configure infrastructure (listeners, pivot listeners) and execute common post-exploitation workflows without hunting through official docs.  
- Covers core Beacon commands and modules for execution, in-memory .NET execution, process injection, token manipulation, Kerberos ticket operations, and credential access (e.g., DCSync/Mimikatz integration).  
- Includes practical guidance for pivoting (SOCKS, CovertVPN), lateral movement (PsExec/WinRM/WMI “jump” and remote-exec), and basic exfil/collection actions (screenshots, keylogging, hashdump).  
- Emphasizes OPSEC: spawnto/ppid spoofing, avoiding default Malleable C2 behavior, and reducing disk/IOC footprint.  
- Useful primarily for red teamers and pentesters running Cobalt Strike, and secondarily for blue teams to understand common operator tradecraft and likely telemetry points.

Technical Focus:
- Cobalt Strike Beacon command set and workflows  
- Listener types (HTTP/HTTPS, DNS, SMB, TCP) and pivoting  
- Malleable C2 profiles (traffic shaping/behavior customization)  
- Process injection & in-memory execution (execute-assembly, dllinject, shinject)  
- Credential access & AD abuse (DCSync, token theft, pass-the-hash)  
- OPSEC controls (spawnto, PPID spoofing, artifact reduction)

Use Cases:
- Quick reference during engagements for Beacon commands and syntax
- Setting up egress and internal pivot listeners (SMB/TCP/DNS) for segmented networks
- Performing lateral movement via jump/remote-exec (PsExec/WinRM/WMI) using stolen/forged tokens
- Tuning stealth via Malleable C2, spawnto, and PPID spoofing before post-exploitation
- Mapping common CS tradecraft to defensive detections and hunting hypotheses

Keywords:
Cobalt Strike, Beacon, C2, listener, HTTP, HTTPS, DNS, SMB, TCP, Malleable C2, Aggressor Script, execute-assembly, powerpick, AMSI bypass, process injection, PPID spoofing, spawnto, DCSync, Mimikatz, pass-the-hash, token impersonation, PsExec, WinRM, WMI, SOCKS4a, CovertVPN, keylogger, screenshot, hashdump, timestomp, AppLocker